<p><b>Chinese alcoholic beverages</b> seem to precede the earliest stages of <a href="/wiki/History_of_China" title="History of China">Chinese civilization</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-roach_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-roach-1">[1]</a></sup> They include <a href="/wiki/Rice_wine" title="Rice wine">rice</a> and grape <a href="/wiki/Wine" title="Wine">wine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Chinese_beer" class="mw-redirect" title="Chinese beer">beer</a>, and various <a href="/wiki/Liquor" class="mw-redirect" title="Liquor">liquors</a> including <i><a href="/wiki/Baijiu" title="Baijiu">baijiu</a></i>, the most-consumed distilled spirit in the world.</p>
